OL,3,CMother's devastation after taking
OL,4,Cepilepsy drug linked to birth defects
OL,6,FResearch suggested that the drug,
OL,7,Fusually sold under the brand name
OL,8,FEpilim could be teratogenic - harmful
OL,9,Fto foetuses.
OL,11,FAccording to the MHRA, babies exposed
OL,12,Fto sodium valproate in the womb have
OL,13,Fan 11% risk of birth defects and a 30-
OL,14,F40% risk of neuro-developmental
OL,15,Fdisabilities, which can be permanent.
OL,17,FOn top of this, a campaign group later
OL,18,Funcovered notes from the drugs
OL,19,Fmanufacture, Sanofi, suggesting it
OL,20,Fknew about the risks as long ago as
OL,21,Fthe 1970s.
